{
  "note": "Upstream provenance lock (churn anti-rot). Per patch, per touched file: the git blob OID (whole-file) PLUS per-hunk anchors {oid, hunks:[{header,range,hash}]} — each hunk's baseline old-side line span hashed at the Firefox tag. `check` diffs vs any ref: identical OID => provably unrotted (skip); OID changed but every hunk hash intact => still apply-safe (edit was OUTSIDE the hunks); a changed hunk => potential conflict; \"absent\" => a file gjoa creates (collision-checked). Legacy bare-string entries still read (degrade to whole-file precision). `digest` = one sha256 over the whole locked surface (baked-identity coordinate; self-verifying — `check` flags a hand-edit). Regenerate after any patch/baseline change: provenance lock.",
